ActivityGroup.definition: A conceptual grouping of activities that occur at the same timepoint (Encounter). In the protocol, this is often represented by a named row or section in the SoA table. In the USDM, this is represented by multiple 'ScheduledActivityInstance' objects sharing the same 'encounterId'.

name.name: name
name.definition: A descriptive name for the group of activities (e.g., 'Screening Procedures'). This may be inferred from the protocol's SoA table structure.

id.name: id
id.definition: A unique identifier for this conceptual group.

activities.name: activities
activities.definition: A list of 'ScheduledActivityInstance' objects that belong to this group.

name.name: name
name.definition: The literal identifier (i.e., distinctive designation) of the timing.

label.name: label
label.definition: The short descriptive designation for the timing.

description.name: description
description.definition: A narrative representation of the chronological relationship between temporal events.

value.name: value
value.definition: The temporal value of the chronological relationship between temporal events.

valueLabel.name: valueLabel
valueLabel.definition: The short descriptive designation for the timing value.

windowLower.name: windowLower
windowLower.definition: The earliest chronological value of an allowable period of time during which a temporal event takes place.

windowUpper.name: windowUpper
windowUpper.definition: The latest chronological value of an allowable period of time during which a temporal event takes place.

windowLabel.name: windowLabel
windowLabel.definition: The short descriptive designation for a time period, or other type of interval, during which a temporal event may be achieved, obtained, or observed.

type.name: type
type.definition: A characterization or classification of the chronological relationship between temporal events.

relativeToFrom.name: relativeToFrom
relativeToFrom.definition: The name of the reference event used to define the temporal relationship with another event.

PlannedTimepoint.definition: Represents a planned timepoint in the study schedule (e.g., 'Visit 1', 'Day 15'). This is the 'when' an activity occurs. In the SoA, this corresponds to a column header.

ActivityTimepoint.definition: A link between an Activity and a PlannedTimepoint, signifying that the activity is performed at that time. In the SoA, this is represented by a checkmark or 'X' at the intersection of an activity row and a timepoint column.

id.name: id
id.definition: A unique identifier for this link.

activityId.name: activityId
activityId.definition: The ID of the Activity being performed.

plannedTimepointId.name: plannedTimepointId
plannedTimepointId.definition: The ID of the PlannedTimepoint when the activity occurs.
